SIMPLE: stamineous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stamineous
<hw>Sta*min"e*ous</hw> <pr>(-m⟦icr⟧n"⟦esl⟧*⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>stamineus</ets>, from <ets>stamen</ets>
thread.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Consisting of stamens or
threads.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the stamens;
possessing stamens; also, attached to the stamens; <as>as, a
<ex>stamineous</ex> nectary</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Staminiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
